<center>
<div class="noprint plainlinksneverexpand navbar" style="background:none; padding:0; font-weight:normal;; font-size:xx-small;">This box: <a href="/wiki/Template:Legal_status" title="Template:Legal status"><span title="View this template" style="">view</span></a>&#160;•&#160;<a href="/wiki/Template_talk:Legal_status" title="Template talk:Legal status"><span title="Discussion about this template" style="">talk</span></a>&#160;•&#160;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Legal_status&amp;action=edit" class="external text" title="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Legal_status&amp;action=edit" rel="nofollow"><span title="Edit this template" style=";">edit</span></a></div>
</center>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Illegal immigration</b> refers to immigration across national borders in a way that violates the immigration laws of the destination country. In politics, the term may imply a larger set of social issues and time constraints with disputed consequences in areas such as economy, social welfare, education, health care, slavery, prostitution, legal protections, voting rights, public services, and human rights. Conversely, <a href="/wiki/Illegal_emigration" title="Illegal emigration">Illegal emigration</a> refers to unlawfully leaving a country.</p>
